    <reapack name="RegionForge.lua" type="script"
             desc="RegionForge — Hierarchical region creation &amp; batch render">
      <metadata>
        <description><![CDATA[
Hierarchical region creation and batch render tool for REAPER.

Creates regions from your track folder structure with per-type wildcard naming
(SFX, Music, Dialogue, Environment), then batch-renders them to organized output
folders. All settings persist between sessions via REAPER ExtState.

Features:
- Wildcard token naming: $prefix, $root, $parent, $bpm, $meter, $character, $questname, $line
- Four built-in audio types with independent configs
- Live hierarchy tree preview on the Main tab
- Batch render with region checklist, Select All / None / Filter by Type
- Output path templates per audio type
        ]]></description>
        <link rel="website">https://github.com/panchuel/Panchu_Scripts</link>
      </metadata>
